# Raw feature collections — committing these would add ~180MB per run to git
# (51 + 38 + 90 MB across MT FWP layers #3, #10, #11). The S02.1 spec at
# docs/planning/epics/E02-geometry-ingestion.md (line 134-138) calls for
# committing both metadata + features fixtures, but assumed "small". Real MT
# data exceeds the assumption by ~3 orders of magnitude.
#
# Until a fixture-storage policy is decided (e.g. git-lfs, object-store
# upload + manifest, or sampling), keep features fixtures local-only.
# Metadata files (~7KB each) ARE committed for drift detection on field
# names, OID columns, and spatialReference.
*-features-*.geojson

# Manifests (S02.7) — *-manifest-*.json
# Per-fetch checksum manifests (~5KB each) ARE committed for cross-operator
# drift detection. Format: {features_count, layer_hash, hash_distribution,
# fetched_at, source_url, source_layer_max_record_count, source_layer_object_id_field}.
# See docs/runbooks/E02-geometry-verification.md for the manifest-diff workflow.
# No glob rule is needed here since manifests don't match *-features-*.geojson —
# this comment exists to anchor the policy.

# Atomic-write tmp files orphaned by interrupted writes (rare).
*.tmp

# Raw PDF source documents — committing these would add ~10MB per fetch to git
# (DEA booklet alone exceeds 5MB across 141 pages; black bear correction is small
# but the cumulative four-PDF set is non-trivial). The S03.1 spec at
# docs/planning/epics/E03-regulation-text-ingestion.md (line 162) calls for
# local-only PDFs paired with a committed per-fetch manifest carrying SHA-256,
# page count, and source provenance — same pattern as the S02.7 ArcGIS-features
# manifest. See docs/planning/epics/E03-regulation-text-ingestion.md S03.1 for
# the full manifest schema (8 fields).
*.pdf

# Drift-detection marker files written when SHA-256 of a re-fetch differs from
# the committed manifest. Operator deletes the marker after acknowledging the
# drift; until then, downstream extraction stories (S03.3-S03.5) refuse to
# proceed. Markers are runtime state, not committed artifacts.
*-pending-reextraction.flag

# Per-PDF manifests (S03.1) — *-pdf-manifest.json
# Per-fetch checksum manifests (~1KB each) ARE committed for cross-operator
# drift detection. Format: {filename, pdf_sha256, page_count, fetched_at,
# source_url, document_type, publication_date, citation_id}.
# No glob rule needed since manifests don't match *.pdf — this comment exists
# to anchor the policy.
